node.text: How to know if you are overthinking it? Best selling author Michelle Rial chats with me about her creative slump, the shower principle, how framing is important, and her new book that’s kinda sad but maybe a little funny, but mostly sad. I promise you will find humor and comfort in Michelle’s simple yet complex translations of what being human feels like. Follow her @michellerial

node.text: For years I have been trying to fit emotions into one image. To locate something universally human. This year, I started a newsletter to explore the complex nature of thoughts and feelings, the things that are too complicated and messy to fit into one image - it’s called “bad at keeping secrets” it’s a newsletter with very little news. I hope it can be a conversation. That we can talk about what it feels like to be human in this moment.

node.text: Do u ever take it personally when people u love are sad?Everyone in my life is sad right now. It’s hard not to wonder if I am holding you back from being happy. My therapist says that I have problems with enmeshment. Have u heard of that? It is when personal boundaries of a relationship are unclear… but it doesn’t stop me from wanting to make u happy… even tho I know I can’t.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Carissa Potter Carlson on August 23, 2021 tagging @peopleiveloved. May be an illustration of one or more people and text that says 'EVERYTHING WILL BE MORE BEAUTIFUL THAN Yo0 CAN IMAGINE, CAN FEEL IT. you DONT HAVE το WORRY ANY MORE.'.

node.text: Is there someone in your life that needs to hear this? This is what my mother told me as she left. Today, in my newsletter (link in bio) I talk about universal basic income, sleeping with my mother and if we have worth inherently as humans just for existing.

node.text: I was listening to @hiddenbrain last week about how marriages are getting harder because in part we expect to get all of our emotional needs met by one person. And this creates unrealistic expectations for our partners.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Carissa Potter Carlson on August 21, 2021. May be a cartoon of one or more people and text that says 'AT TIMES, 1 SAYING HOW OU REALLY FEEL IS 'NOT'IN YOUR BEST INTEREST.'.

node.text: I have been thinking a lot about this. I was raised to say whatever it is that I was feeling because it was what I was feeling and true. But sometimes this is not the best... and I don't know where the line is. Help.
